Retrieve data from API "Poisson"

Source: R/get_poisson.R
get_poisson_observations.Rd

Available endpoint:

  • get_poisson_observations retrieves data of scientific fishery operations

See the API documentation for available filter parameters: https://hubeau.eaufrance.fr/page/api-poisson

get_poisson_observations(
  params,
  cfg = config::get(file = system.file("config.yml", package = "hubeau"))
)

Arguments

params

a list the list of parameters of the queries and their values in the format list(ParamName = "Param value", ...), use the function get_available_params for a list of the available query parameters for a given API endpoint and see the API documentation for their descriptions

cfg

a config object describing the configuration of the APIs. Use the internal package configuration by default configuration

Value

a tibble::tibble with all available parameters in columns.

See also

doApiQuery for more details on the API querying process.

Examples

# Get the query parameters for the requested API/endpoint
get_available_params(api = "poisson",
                     endpoint = "observations")

# Retrieve selected fields on a river fish sampled in Brest
library(dplyr)
#> 
#> Attaching package: ‘dplyr’
#> The following objects are masked from ‘package:stats’:
#> 
#>     filter, lag
#> The following objects are masked from ‘package:base’:
#> 
#>     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
fields <- paste("code_operation",
                "date_operation",
                "libelle_point_prelevement_aspe",
                "effectif_lot",
                "code_alternatif_taxon",
                sep = ",")
brest_fishes <- get_poisson_observations(
  list(
    libelle_commune = "Brest",
    fields = fields
    )
 ) %>%
 group_by_at(vars(-effectif_lot)) %>%
   summarise(nb_individals = sum(effectif_lot))
#> `summarise()` has grouped output by 'code_operation', 'date_operation',
#> 'libelle_point_prelevement_aspe'. You can override using the `.groups`
#> argument.
